Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, core and dice @green bell pepper{1}(core and dice into 1/2-inch pieces). Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Drain and rinse @black beans{1%can}. Quarter @lime{1%unit}.

In a large #bowl{}, toss together bell pepper, tomato, scallions, beans, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @fajita spice blend{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, juice from three lime wedges, and pepper until well combined. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, 1 tsp Fajita Spice Blend, 2 tsp salt, and juice from six lime wedges.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @fajita spice blend{2%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

> You can swap in chicken or salmon for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked
> through, 3-5 minutes per side, or salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp,
> 5-7 minutes. Flip salmon and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

Add @butter{1%tbsp} to pan with pork; baste pork with melted butter until thoroughly coated.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter.

Transfer pork to a #cutting board{} to rest at least ~{3%minutes}.

> You can start plating the potatoes and salad while the pork rests.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, potato wedges, and salad between plates in separate sections. Drizzle any remaining butter from pan over pork. Serve.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!).

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.